703377f-a.text:
Bush Street, north side, east from a point west of Hicks Street (seen in the foreground) showing an area soon to be demolished because of the Federal grants making possible the Red Hook slum clearance and the building of low cost housing apartments. Also shown is 805-823 Hicks Street, east side, noth from Bush Street.
June 9, 1938.
F. L. Sperr
